jobInfoModel.sanitizedJobDescription:
Purpose: As lead of a software team, will be working in a self-motivated, fast paced environment, to design, implement, and maintain embedded controls’ firmware and Standard Operating Procedures.

Key Focus Areas:

  • · Programming
  • · Documentation Control
  • · Communications
  • · Trouble Shooting
  • · Documentation
  • · Research

Programming

  • · Coding: Write coding for new products and maintain and modify code for existing products using embedded C programming/Web programming
  • · Perform unit and integration testing
  • · Conduct Software requirements analysis, software risk analysis, & software performance analysis
  • · Record and adhere to software design specifications
  • · Maintain standards compliance

Documentation Control

  • · Maintain Standard Operating Procedures
  • · Maintain software design documentation
  • · Lead software design review

Communications

  • · Intra departmental
  • Peer review, consulting and follow-through on department objectives and deadlines
  • Recording and reporting
  • · Inter departmental
  • Production schedule – notifications
  • Work closely with Systems Hardware Design Engineers to collaborate on hardware/software systems integration
  • Participate in and follow product through all stages of product life cycle

Troubleshooting

  • Research and solve cross functional design/production issues
  • Work with Engineering, Quality, Production and other professional staff members to resolve discrepancies and variations as may occur relative to manufacturing process and/or test instructions, shop packet, and quality.

ESSENTIAL COMPETENCIES AND HIRING REQUISITES

Education: Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering or Computer Engineering required.

Experience: Participation in academic projects or work assignments involving the development of embedded firmware in C language or web application development required. 2+ years of professional experience in development of embedded firmware in C language, working experience of PIC microprocessors and knowledge of electronic hardware design preferred.

Essential Skills:

  • Possesses motor skills- aptitude for using various basic shop tools;
  • Possesses verbal intelligence - understand the meaning of words and respond effectively;
  • Computer skills and literacy sufficient to access, correct, input and search data and information and prepare reports;
  • Numerical intelligence - mathematical skills, read and interpret instruments and test equipment; skillful to recognize, read and work reliably with sequential alpha-numeric designations as contained in, work orders, prints, product codes, lot numbers;
  • Spatial relationship aptitude; able to read mechanical prints and schematics
  • Conflict resolution skills – recognizes and intervenes to deescalate conflict in a timely manner
  • Leadership skills – mentors, coaches and inspires others to overcome obstacles, persevere in efforts, accept accountability for and execute responsibilities; personal behavior elicits respect, responsiveness from others.

KEY SUCCESS FACTORS:

  • Quality
  • Productivity of work team
  • Accuracy, timeliness and thoroughness of records and reports
  • Judgment exercised in problem solving
  • Knowledge of and consistent enforcement of company policies

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $80,000.00 - $120,000.00 per year

Benefits:

  • 401(k)
  • Dental insurance
  • Employee assistance program
  • Flexible spending account
  • Health insurance
  • Health savings account
  • Paid time off
  • Referral program
  • Retirement plan
  • Tuition reimbursement
  • Vision insurance

Schedule:

  • 8 hour shift
  • Day shift
  • Monday to Friday

Supplemental pay types:

  • Bonus pay

Education:

  • Bachelor's (Required)

Experience:

  • Embedded software: 4 years (Required)
  • C++: 3 years (Required)

Work Location: In person
